############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The interval notation tells us to graph all numbers between [`[$a]`] and [`\infty\text{.}`] So the shading can start at [`[$a]`] and go all the way to the right "to [`\infty`]". There should be a parenthesis at [`[$a]`] to indicate that [`[$a]`] itself is not included.

>> [@image(insertGraph($image_1), width=>600)@]*  <<

We have shaded all numbers greater than [`[$a]\text{.}`] So in set-builder notation, the interval is [`[$set_builder]\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

